<Layout
  title="Termite Inspection Palmerston | Slab-on-Ground + Bushland Boundary | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Termite inspection and barrier work for Palmerston NT — Bakewell, Bellamack, Durack, Farrar, Gunn, Johnston, Rosebery, Zuccoli. Slab-on-ground reticulation life, Mastotermes ingress from Litchfield bush, AS 3660 / AS 4349.3. NT Pest Control licensed.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://darwintermitebarriers.com.au/palmerston/">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Bakewell &middot; Bellamack &middot; Durack &middot; Gunn &middot; Zuccoli</span>
      <h1>Termite inspection in <span class="accent">Palmerston</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Palmerston is Greater Darwin&rsquo;s satellite city &mdash; 25 minutes
        south-east of the CBD, population around 40,000 and still growing through
        Mitchell and Zuccoli. The stock is mostly slab-on-ground brick veneer
        from the 2000s&ndash;2010s with steel-frame newer builds. Termite risk
        looks lower than the older Top End stock but the bushland boundary
        problem is real: Mastotermes pushes in from the surrounding scrub on
        any block backing onto reserve.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book an inspection</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Palmerston</span>
      <h2>The Palmerston termite story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Slab-on-ground reticulation tubes &mdash; check the life remaining.</h3>
        <p>
          Most Palmerston homes built between 2002 and 2018 had a chemical
          reticulation system installed under or around the slab as part of the
          AS 3660.1 pre-construction barrier. The Form 16 Termite Management
          Certificate (filed under the meter box or in the electrical sub-board)
          will state the chemical used and the expected life: 8&ndash;10 years for
          Termidor SC, 10&ndash;12 years for Premise 200SC, 5 years for older
          permethrin-based products. <strong>If your home was built between 2002
          and 2014, your reticulation is at or past end of life right now.</strong>
          Renewal can be done by re-injecting the existing tube (cheap, $1,800&ndash;
          $2,800) or by replacing with a fresh perimeter chemical barrier
          ($3,200&ndash;$5,500). We confirm at inspection.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Newer Zuccoli / Mitchell stock &mdash; physical barriers + builders&rsquo; gaps.</h3>
        <p>
          Estates released since around 2015 (Zuccoli, Mitchell, eastern Bellamack)
          mostly use <strong>physical barriers</strong> (Kordon, HomeGuard,
          Termimesh) at slab penetrations instead of, or alongside, chemical
          reticulation. Physical barriers don&rsquo;t expire &mdash; they fail
          when builders skip a step. Most common failures we see at pre-purchase
          inspections: missed gaps at electrical conduit penetrations, mortar
          bridging at brick veneer ground-courses (termites tunnel through the
          unreinforced mortar joint above the barrier), and damp-proof course
          gaps at the slab edge. None of these show up in a visual inspection
          done from outside &mdash; you need sub-roof + sub-floor + perimeter scan
          with moisture-meter readings.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Bushland-boundary blocks &mdash; Mastotermes pressure from Litchfield.</h3>
        <p>
          Palmerston pushes south-east into Litchfield Council where the
          surrounding country is heavily wooded acreage with mature eucalypt
          stands &mdash; classic Mastotermes habitat. Any Palmerston block backing
          onto reserve (large parts of Marlow Lagoon, Yarrawonga, Driver, and
          the southern edge of Zuccoli/Mitchell) has Mastotermes pressure from
          outside the property. Mastotermes colonies routinely send foraging
          tunnels 200&ndash;300m through soil, so a colony in surrounding bush
          can reach your perimeter even if you haven&rsquo;t touched it. We
          recommend annual inspection minimum on these boundary blocks; baiting
          systems work especially well because Mastotermes happily takes bait
          back to the colony.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Body-corporate compliance for Palmerston townhouses + units.</h3>
        <p>
          Palmerston has a substantial body-corporate sector &mdash; townhouse
          complexes in Bakewell, Driver, Gray and Moulden, plus newer unit
          developments along Roystonea Avenue. Strata-titled complexes should
          run an annual AS 3660.2 inspection of common property to maintain the
          chemical-barrier warranty and the Form 16 paperwork from original
          construction. Many older Palmerston townhouse complexes have lapsed
          warranty because annual inspections were skipped. We do these as a
          half-day audit of common areas, slab penetrations, garden edges and
          any timber landscaping. Cost varies by complex size: $450&ndash;$1,100.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Palmerston jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>AS 4349.3 pre-purchase inspection on a Bakewell brick veneer ($480&ndash;$680)</li>
          <li>Annual AS 3660.2 inspection on a Zuccoli physical-barrier home ($350&ndash;$450)</li>
          <li>Reticulation renewal on 2008-built Durack home ($1,800&ndash;$2,800)</li>
          <li>Sentricon Always Active bait install on Marlow Lagoon bushland-boundary block ($2,400&ndash;$3,600)</li>
          <li>Body-corporate annual inspection of 24-unit Driver townhouse complex ($600&ndash;$1,100)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

